question:
Allie and Betty play a game where they take turns rolling a standard die. If a player rolls $n$, she is awarded $g(n)$ points, where  \[g(n) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl} 8 & \text{ if }n\text{ is a multiple of 2 and 4}, \\
3 & \text{ if }n\text{ is only a multiple of 2}, \\
1 & \text{ if }n\text{ is not a multiple of 2}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Allie rolls the die five times and gets a 6, 3, 4, 2, and 2. Betty rolls and gets 8, 1, 1, 2, and 4. What is the product of Allie's total points and Betty's total points?

If $a = \frac{3}{5}$ and $b = \frac{7}{9}$, express the value of the following as a common fraction: $$
\frac{\frac{a}{1+b}}{\frac{b}{1+a}}
$$
